The paper discusses the detection of cyber attacks in industrial process networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a visualization system for analyzing the sensor data from these networks, which involves techniques from information visualization (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of detecting attacks in a periodical behavior, which could fall under the category of control theory (cs.CY). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness and usability of the system, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
